---

<Base
  title="Facelift in Houston, Texas | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Facelift in Houston, Texas at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Facelift in Houston, Texas"
  headerImage="/img/facelift-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/houston-facelift"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                While everyone ages slightly differently, everyone experiences wrinkling of the skin and deflation of the soft tissues of the face with age. Different facelift techniques can be used to turn back the clock on aging and restore youthfulness to your face.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What do you want from a Facelift in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery, Dr. Danielle Andry, 
                                    and Dr. Nandi Wijay believe
                                    in performing natural-looking facial rejuvenation techniques that gracefully restore your natural beauty, staying away
                                    from techniques that give patients a wind-blown or “frozen face” look.  The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery
                                    use techniques that conceal scars without dramatically changing or creating step-offs in the hairline that are tell-tale
                                    signs of having a facelift.  The goal of The Oaks Plastic Surgery is to make your face and neckline look rejuvenated and
                                    refreshed without looking like you’ve been to see a plastic surgeon.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Additionally, the plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery want to achieve the best result possible with each of their patients. Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay believe in treating each patient individually and tailoring your facelift to fit your needs.  If you have excess skin or sagging of your neck, this will be included along with your facelift procedure to provide the best result possible.  Additionally, if you and your plastic surgeon feel that you could benefit from using your own fat to help restore volume to your cheeks or other areas of your face, this will also be included along with your facelift procedure.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why do you want a Facelift in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    If you find yourself using your index finger and thumb to pull up on your face in the mirror, wishing you could just keep your face in
                                    that position, you may be a candidate for a facelift.  Patients commonly complain of wrinkles in the face, descent of the cheek tissues,
                                    and fullness along the chin and jawline called jowls.  Additionally, patients complain of neck banding, double chin, or “turkey neck”.
                                    A facelift can help turn back the clock and reverse the effects of gravity over the years.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed along with a Facelift in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    As discussed, your facelift may be performed along with neck lift and/or fat transfer to help restore volume and youthfulness to the face.
                                    Additionally, facelift is often performed with <a href="//blepharoplasty-surgery-houston">upper eyelid surgery</a> or <a href="//blepharoplasty-surgery-houston">lower eyelid surgery</a> (upper blepharoplasty or lower blepharoplasty),
                                    <a href="/houston-eyebrow-lift">brow lift</a>, and/or <a href="/houston-botox">botox</a>, <a href="/fillers-houston">fillers</a>, or <a href="/chemical-peel-houston">chemical peel</a>.  Prior to and following your facelift procedure, it is important to develop a good skin
                                    care regimen that helps to fight signs of aging everyday.  The plastic surgeons and staff at The Oaks Plastic Surgery can help you find
                                    products that will help keep your skin looking young and fresh and reverse some of the harmful effects of the environment on your skin.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect during your initial consultation for a Facelift in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    If you are considering a facelift  in Houston, Texas, an appointment can be made with one of the plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery,
                                    Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay.  You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your
                                    consultation, your plastic surgeon will:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals </li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy</li>
                                    <li>Discuss recommendations regarding cosmetic surgical or nonsurgical techniques that may help you achieve your goals</li>
                                    <li>If a facelift is the right plastic surgery procedure for you, your plastic surgeon will discuss details of the the plastic surgery procedures that are offered and which plastic surgery approach is right for you </li>
                                    <li>Preoperative photographs will be taken </li>
                                    <li>The risks and benefits of a facelift and any additional plastic surgery procedures will be thoroughly outlined for you</li>
                                    <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both our plastic surgeons and plastic surgery staff regarding a facelift and any other cosmetic surgical or nonsurgical procedures you may be interested in</li>
                                    <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the cosmetic procedure including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after facelift surgery</li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
